                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">484.11 Young, Reuben S., No. 2/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Southard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-04T11:00:00+02:35"
                            >August 4, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—4:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. I have seen the Emperor and reviewed with him the Department’s telegram of
                    July 20, 8 p.m. He is unwilling to give definite answer until Foreign Office
                    shall have had time to reconsider claims on the basis of the representations
                    authorized by the Department’s telegram of July 20, 8 p.m. I have impressed upon
                    His Majesty that further undue delay will be considered inexcusable. I hope to
                    have definite answer for report within 2 weeks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
